\subsection{Balance Sheet}
% -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Assets are economic resources with the potential to provide future economic benefits to a firm.\par

Liabilities are creditors' claims. Creditors have provided funds, or goods and services, and
the firm has an obligation to pay creditors for those goods and services.\par

Shareholders' equity shows the amount of funds owners have provided either by buying
shares or by reinvesting (retaining) the net assets generated by earnings.

Retained earnings represent the net assets (= total assets − total liabilities) a firm derives
from its earnings that exceed the dividends it has distributed to shareholders.

